laboratory_examinations.findings: Opening pressure of 14 cm of water; clear cerebrospinal fluid with glucose level of 64 mg/dL and protein level of 65 mg/dL; the cell count had 1 red cell and 1 white cell per cubic millimeter (25% neutrophils, 50% lymphocytes, 25% monocytes). A spun Gram’s stain showed no organisms and culture had no growth.
Continuous focal slowing in the right hemisphere, no epileptiform activity present.
Imaging showed volume loss, scattered white-matter changes, and lacunar infarcts; reduced diffusion in frontal, right parietal and temporal cortexes and in the right caudate nucleus.

laboratory_examinations.procedure_name: Vitamin B12 and Homocysteine level test
laboratory_examinations.findings: Serum level of vitamin B12 was 416 pg/mL (307 pmol/L) and homocysteine was 8.9 µmol/L.
Negative for substances including bismuth and lithium.
